  "body": "## Description\r\n\r\nThe validator client is presently using dummy values for the `domain` parameter required for BLS signatures.\r\n\r\nDetermining this value requires knowledge of the current [`Fork`](https://github.com/ethereum/eth2.0-specs/blob/dev/specs/core/0_beacon-chain.md#fork) struct for the present `BeaconState`. See ['get_domain'](https://github.com/ethereum/eth2.0-specs/blob/dev/specs/core/0_beacon-chain.md#get_domain) for more info on domain generation.\r\n\r\nCurrently, the val client has no way of reading this info from the beacon node. We should provide the capability from the `BeaconNode` traits in the val client, and eventually add the functionality to the GRPC interface.\r\n\r\n## Expected Behaviour\r\n\r\n- Allow for the val client to pull the required fork data from the beacon node.\r\n- Ensure all signatures in the val client use this fork data.\r\n\r\n\r\n## Additional Info\r\n\r\nWe could consider two different methods for the validator to get this info:\r\n\r\n1. Request the `domain` from the beacon node (for some supplied `epoch` and `domain_type`).\r\n2. Request the `Fork` info form the beacon node and generate the domain locally.\r\n\r\nI'm leaning towards (1) at the moment, as it keeps more logic in the beacon node. Open to alternative suggestions.",
